1. Install distro
2. ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "email@address.com"
3. the ssh keypair will be store in the current shell location.
4. copy the public key into vultr menu as part of the distro installation process.
5. ssh root@address.
6. Enter pwd provided by vultr.
7. adduser user
8. usermod -aG sudo user
9. ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "email@address.com" (Choose different file name,)
10. cd to ~/user
11. touch authorized_keys
12. mkdir .ssh
13. type C:\Users\user\.ssh\vultr\id_ed25519vultr1 | ssh dell@address "cat >> /home/user/.ssh/authorized_keys"
14. enter the new user's password when loggin in as the new user.

